	"hints": {
		"1": "Ktisis can autosave your poses, even when you disconnect! You can enable them in the Config window.",
		"2": "'Ktisis' is an Ancient Greek term referring to the act of creation, founding, or construction. Its adjective form is 'ktistic.'",
		"3": "Pose responsibly! Incognito Mode will hide any player names when taking photos of your UI.",
		"4": "Turn on the lights! Ktisis can make its own lights, or edit those created from the vanilla GPose window.",
		"5": "You can have over 40 actors in the workspace at once - this limit doesn't extend to lights and other entities.",
		"6": "Did you know? SimpleTweaks has an option to temporarily increase your resolution for more detailed screenshots!",
		"7": "Weapons spawn attached to certain bones on players' skeletons, but you can attach players and other objects to different bones too.",
		"8": "Ctrl+Click lets you select multiple objects at once, and Shift+Clicking in the Workspace selects all entities between two points.",
		"9": "With multiple entities selected, the different Transform types (parallel, inverse, mirrored) let you modify them simultaneously.",
		"10": "New actors don't have to be copies of your player character - you can import other NPCs or PCs from the overworld too.",
		"11": "Tired of sitting+standing to reset your animation? The Actor Editor lets you reset or pick any animation/idle to play on any actor.",
		"12": "Ahmi is the default Pose View character, but you can swap these for your own images using the templates in the Config window.",
		"13": "Many installs of ReShade contain a Chroma Key shader, which lets you green-screen a perfectly transparent background for your images.",
		"14": "Even mid-way through a pose, you can load a vanilla facial expression using the Actor Editor's Pose Expressions feature.",
		"15": "Reference poses can be overlaid directly in-game to help you get the angles just right.",
		"16": "The Camera Editor includes an Orthographic setting, letting you photograph scenes from a tilt-shift perspective.",
		"17": "NPC appearances can be imported just like .chara files, or applied through another plugin like Glamourer instead.",
		"18": "Ktisis works with other plugins through IPC, including: Penumbra collections, Glamourer designs, and C+ templates.",
		"19": "Overlay bubbles (and these hints!) are drawn in vanilla using KamiToolKit, the same library powering the VanillaPlus plugin.",
		"20": "Have a suggestion or encounter a bug? Send them to our Discord server!",
		"21": "Spot Lights and Area Lights can have a texture loaded in front of them to apply different colors and effects - we call these gobos!",
		"22": "You can click the center dot of a translation gizmo to move an actor in 3D - holding Shift will snap them onto terrain in the world!",
		"23": "The Actor Editor's animation controls let you apply animations onto different parts of the body, like talking animations for lips.",
		"24": "If you use an emote that spawns a prop object (like /tomestone), it can be posed with Ktisis like any weapon.",
		"25": "The Actor Editor's equipment tab also lets you equip non-weapon props, such as: job stones, wine bottles, books, and Nidhogg's eye.",
		"26": "Overworld objects edited by Ktisis are only temporarily changed - their hitboxes and collision data also remain intact.",
		"27": "Different bodies of water will use the Water Editor's sliders for different purposes - play around to see which affects where!",
		"28": "Inverse Kinematics can change the positions of limbs in and out of posing mode, even while animations are playing.",
		"29": "Non-human actors may be compatible with Gaze Control, including minions and monsters.",
		"30": "You can change many of the colors for Ktisis' overlay (gizmo, bones, workspace categories) in the Config > Personalization section.",
		"31": "Hair and faces belong to different partial skeletons than the main body, just like some helmets and chest pieces.",
		"32": "The orb/arrows used for posing is called a Gizmo, and gets drawn by the ImGuizmo tool for ImGui!",
		"33": "You can change the positions at which bones appear using Bone Offsets, which are useful for close-together clusters like facial bones.",
		"34": "You can dismiss these hints by left-clicking them, or disable them entirely in the settings.",
		"35": "The scrollwheel lets you move Ktisis' colored transform sliders one tick at a time, or faster/slower by holding Shift or Control.",
		"36": "Since updates made in FFXIV Dawntrail, face-expression poses may only load correctly on the race/gender they were created with.",
		"37": "The vanilla GPose menu has a button to add stickers over your screen - try them out for different icons, emojis and text.",
		"38": "There's over 280 possible character portraits to display along with these hints.",
		"39": "Too many windows? Try the alternate Ktisis Toolbar UI in your settings menu!"
	}
}
